SIMPLE: enactment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enactment
<hw>En*act"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
passing of a bill into a law; the giving of legislative sanction and
executive approval to a bill whereby it is established as a
law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is enacted or passed into a law; a law; a
decree; a statute; a prescribed requirement; <as>as, a prohibitory
<ex>enactment</ex>; a social <ex>enactment</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enactor</ent>⟦br⟧
